@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" /> <!-- Link to external CSS file -->
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

        <p>Welcome to the jungle of privacy! Here at the Wild Zoo, we take privacy as seriously as we take feeding our pandas. That's pretty serious, believe us.</p>

        <h2>What Information Do We Collect?</h2>
        <p>We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and phone number when you embark on a wild journey with us. Don't worry, we won't ask for your spirit animal.</p>

        <h2>How Do We Use Your Information?</h2>
        <p>Your information helps us keep track of who's who in our animal kingdom and allows us to provide you with the best possible experience. Rest assured, your data is as safe as a lion in its den.</p>

        <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We won't sell your info to any pesky poachers. We only share it with trusted partners who help us maintain the zoo, and they're sworn to secrecy. Cross our hearts and hope to be hugged by a baby elephant.</p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>We've built a digital fortress around your data, guarded by tech-savvy gorillas and cyber-savvy parrots. No unauthorized access allowed - unless you're a monkey with a knack for hacking.</p>

        <h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>Just like the animal kingdom, our privacy policy may evolve over time. We'll keep you informed of any major changes, so stay tuned to our jungle drums!</p>

        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, don't hesitate to let us know. We promise not to release the hounds.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
